---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MemoryCard from '../components/MemoryCard.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Carnegie | Private relationship memory in development"
  description="Carnegie is a private personal CRM concept and product in development for remembering people, context, and meaningful interactions over time."
  lang="en"
>
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Private product in development</p>
      <h1 id="hero-title">A private memory system for relationships, currently in development.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Carnegie is being built to help its owner/team remember who people
        are, what matters to them, and how relationships change over time.
        Access is private and not open to the public.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Primary actions">
        <a class="button" href="mailto:hello@carnegie.app">Contact the team</a>
        <a class="text-link" href="#idea">See the idea</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <MemoryCard lang="en" />
  </section>

  <section class="idea" id="idea" aria-labelledby="idea-title">
    <p class="section-kicker">The idea</p>
    <h2 id="idea-title">A calmer place for relationship context.</h2>
    <div class="idea-grid">
      <article>
        <h3>Keep notes clear</h3>
        <p>
          Separate enduring details from recent context, so relationship
          notes stay useful instead of becoming a messy document.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Remember the moments</h3>
        <p>
          Log meaningful conversations, meetings, calls, and moments in a
          simple timeline you can return to when it matters.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>Find the thread</h3>
        <p>
          Return to people, notes, and moments from one place, without
          relying on memory or spreadsheets.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>See connections quietly</h3>
        <p>
          Understand how people relate to each other without turning your
          relationships into a public social platform.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="principles" id="principles" aria-labelledby="principles-title">
    <div>
      <p class="section-kicker">Principles</p>
      <h2 id="principles-title">Built for thoughtful recall.</h2>
    </div>
    <ul>
      <li>Private access only; Carnegie is not open to the public.</li>
      <li>Owned by you, not shaped around a social feed.</li>
      <li>Quiet enough for personal life, structured enough for professional life.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="closing" aria-labelledby="closing-title">
    <h2 id="closing-title">Remember the people who matter.</h2>
    <p>
      Carnegie presents an idea and product being built for private
      relationship memory, with access limited to its owner/team.
    </p>
    <a class="button" href="mailto:hello@carnegie.app">Contact about Carnegie</a>
  </section>
</Layout>
